This paper discusses data clustering, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The comparison between fuzzy clustering and hard clustering algorithms involves mathematical and statistical analysis, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.DM). The use of fuzzy logic is also relevant to the field of soft computing (cs.SI). Finally, the study of clustering algorithms is often applied to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data analysis in general.
